  Tumblr   linkedin   stumble   Digg   reddit   Newsvine Permalink http://p.dw.com/p/1IPwf EU blacklist Finance ministers also agreed to add Saint Kitts and Nevis, the US Virgin Islands and the Bahamas, to a blacklist of international tax havens, while removing Bahrain, the Marshall Islands and Saint Lucia. The EU drew up the list in December as part of an effort to curb tax avoidance. There are currently nine countries flagged there, while a separate "gray" list includes 62 jurisdictions that have committed to change their practices and cooperate with the EU. Bahrain was one of the states removed from the blacklist Anguilla, the British Virgin Islands, Dominica and Antigua and Barbuda were added to the gray list on Tuesday. Countries on the blacklist could be subject EU funding restrictions, but member states do not agree on whether sanctions should also be implemented. nm/kms (Reuters, dpa) Each evening at 1830 UTC, DW's editors send out a selection of the day's hard news and quality feature journalism. You can sign up to receive it directly here.